# Project Intelligence

## File Organization Patterns
- Public and admin pages separated into distinct directories
- CSS files organized in /css directory
- Images stored in /images directory
- JavaScript files stored in /js directory

## Development Patterns
- Using Tailwind CSS utility classes for styling
- Maintaining consistent file naming conventions
- Separating concerns between public and admin views
- Using package.json for dependency management

## Workflow Insights
- Prefer using npm scripts for build processes
- Maintain documentation in memory-bank directory
- Use consistent indentation (2 spaces) across files
- Follow semantic HTML structure

## Best Practices
- Keep Tailwind configuration in tailwind.config.js
- Process CSS through input.css
- Maintain clean separation between content and presentation
- Document all major decisions in memory bank
